item.title: How to remove objects that are not On the objects place
item.dc:creator: @viruz_3 viruz 3
item.description:
@viruz_3 wrote:

oh… Lol sorry … You gotta find the objects X and Y. then add an delete objects void… Like this:

public void deletethisobject(int objectX, int objectY) {
     ReplaceObject2(objectX, objectY, 6951, -1, 10);
}

And to implement…
Add this into another void called RemoveTheseObjects() ::

public void RemoveTheseObjects() {
     deletethisobject(objectX, objectY);
}

Add that where all your other voids are and add this also to a boolean called process.
And to do that:
Search for: boolean process
and add this under it:

RemoveTheseObjects();

And then your done…

Let me know of the errors please. Or if you just need help.
